🧰 Wiring Instructions
==========================================================
🛠️ Components You'll Need
- Arduino Uno
- 4x4 Keypad
- 16x2 LCD or I2C LCD
- Jumper wires
- Breadboard
- Optional: Resistors, power supply
==========================================================
🔢 Keypad (4x4)
- Rows (R1–R4) → Arduino pins D5, D4, D3, D2
- Columns (C1–C4) → Arduino pins A3, A2, A1, A0
==========================================================
📺 LCD (16x2 in 4-bit mode)
Great choice! Using an I2C LCD with your Arduino calculator simplifies wiring and frees up digital pins. Here’s everything you need to get started:

🔌 I2C LCD Wiring (16x2)
| I2C Pin | Function | Arduino Pin | 
|   GND   | Ground   |     GND     | 
|   VCC   | Power    |      V5     | 
|   SDA   | Data Line|      A4     | 
|   SCL   |Clock Line|      A5     | 

Note: These are standard I2C pins for Arduino Uno. If you're using a different board, the SDA/SCL pins may vary.
===========================================================


